From 27bbc4cd223ee423917bcbb7df57ebe6b93d4f82 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 14:25:26 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] nvkms: VESA DisplayID/DSC/VSDB spec-correctness fixes for
 VR HMDs

Four independent conformance fixes that let high-resolution VR-HMD panels
(HP Reverb G2 and other WMR headsets) enumerate their native modes:

- DisplayID 2.0 Type-VII: walk descriptors by spec stride
  (sizeof(desc) + payload_bytes_len) instead of only when payload_bytes_len == 0,
  which silently dropped every descriptor on payload-bearing blocks (the G2's
  4320x2160 native mode vanished). NVIDIA bug 5923212.  [nvt_displayid20.c]
- DSC PPS: correct the RC QP tables (rows 9-14) and ofs_und8[11] to the VESA
  DSC 1.1 RC model; the prior values broke the 90 Hz DSC handshake.  [nvt_dsc_pps.c]
- DSC flatnessDetThresh: derive from bits_per_component per the DSC PPS; the two
  DP sites used a bitsPerPixelX16-based shift NVIDIA's own comment flagged wrong.
  [nvkms-evo3.c, nvkms-evo4.c]
- MSFT VSDB: read primaryUseCase for VSDB version >= 1 (a fixed field present in
  every version; WMR HMDs ship version 1), so VR headsets are identified.
  [nvt_edidext_861.c]

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
